<div class="col five-sm clear">
<h2 id="section-top">Overview</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContente9d2e182474742fabbdc71ad05931412">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="TGCG Logo" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=11254"/>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Award-Winning Home Care Delivered by Expert Professional Carers</strong></p>
<p>The Good Care Group is a professional provider of high quality home care services that enable older people to stay safely and happily at home for as long as possible with choice and independence, whilst dramatically enhancing overall wellbeing and quality of life.   We provide a range of highly personalised home care services, including 24 hour live in care, day care (in London only) and a respite service, for those family carers who require that much-needed break from caring for a loved one.</p>
<p>Our expertly trained professional carers provide a range of personalised services in your home, everything from companionship, personal care, domestic support, cooking, lifestyle and social activities through to the management and support of specialist conditions.  We also care and support those living with MS and Motor Neurone Disease, as well as those recovering from a stroke or post-operative rehabilitation or those needing a palliative care programme. </p>
<p>All our professional carers are employed by us, which means you can be assured of high quality, continuous care delivered by an expertly trained carer with whom you can build a long term relationship with. The service you receive is fully managed by an expert dedicated regional care team, which means you and our carer have access to unrivalled support and expertise, any time providing total peace of mind, for everyone. </p>
<p>We specialise in care of conditions that affect older people and have won an industry award for innovative delivery of dementia care in the home, using the ground-breaking SPECAL method that enables an individual to live well with dementia and maintain quality of life.  Carers have experience of dementia care and are all highly trained by us, with input from leading dementia charities to ensure they are equipped with the knowledge and skills to effectively support and manage their client’s needs.</p>
<p> </p>
